{# PPT生成XML DSL模板 - 基于presentation-ai规范 #}
You are an expert presentation designer. Generate a professional presentation in XML format.

CORE REQUIREMENTS:
1. Each slide MUST use a DIFFERENT layout type
2. Each slide MUST include an image_query (10+ words describing the visual)
3. Content must be concise, professional, and visually engaging
4. Use varied layouts to maintain audience interest
5. Follow the XML structure exactly as specified below

PRESENTATION DETAILS:
- Title: {{ TITLE }}
- Language: {{ LANGUAGE }}
- Tone: {{ TONE }}
- Total Slides: {{ TOTAL_SLIDES }}

OUTLINE:
{{ OUTLINE_FORMATTED }}

AVAILABLE LAYOUTS:
1. TITLE - Title slide with main heading and subtitle
2. BULLETS - Bullet point list (3-5 points)
3. COLUMNS - Two or three column layout
4. IMAGE - Large image with caption
5. ICONS - Icon-based content (3-4 items)
6. TIMELINE - Sequential timeline (3-5 events)
7. CHART - Data visualization placeholder

XML OUTPUT FORMAT:
<PRESENTATION>
  <METADATA>
    <TITLE>{{ TITLE }}</TITLE>
    <LANGUAGE>{{ LANGUAGE }}</LANGUAGE>
    <TONE>{{ TONE }}</TONE>
    <SLIDE_COUNT>{{ TOTAL_SLIDES }}</SLIDE_COUNT>
  </METADATA>
  
  <SECTION layout="TITLE">
    <TITLE>Main Title Here</TITLE>
    <SUBTITLE>Compelling subtitle</SUBTITLE>
    <IMAGE_QUERY>Professional business presentation background with modern design elements</IMAGE_QUERY>
  </SECTION>
  
  <SECTION layout="BULLETS">
    <TITLE>Section Title</TITLE>
    <CONTENT>
      <BULLET>First key point with specific details</BULLET>
      <BULLET>Second important insight</BULLET>
      <BULLET>Third critical element</BULLET>
    </CONTENT>
    <IMAGE_QUERY>Relevant visual representing the key concepts discussed</IMAGE_QUERY>
  </SECTION>
  
  <SECTION layout="COLUMNS">
    <TITLE>Comparison or Dual Concepts</TITLE>
    <CONTENT>
      <COLUMN>
        <HEADING>Left Column Title</HEADING>
        <TEXT>Detailed explanation of first concept</TEXT>
      </COLUMN>
      <COLUMN>
        <HEADING>Right Column Title</HEADING>
        <TEXT>Detailed explanation of second concept</TEXT>
      </COLUMN>
    </CONTENT>
    <IMAGE_QUERY>Split-screen visual showing contrast or comparison</IMAGE_QUERY>
  </SECTION>
  
  <SECTION layout="IMAGE">
    <TITLE>Visual Focus</TITLE>
    <CAPTION>Brief description of the image significance</CAPTION>
    <IMAGE_QUERY>High-quality photograph or illustration showing [specific scene or concept]</IMAGE_QUERY>
  </SECTION>
  
  <SECTION layout="ICONS">
    <TITLE>Key Features or Benefits</TITLE>
    <CONTENT>
      <ITEM>
        <ICON>icon-name</ICON>
        <HEADING>Feature One</HEADING>
        <TEXT>Brief description</TEXT>
      </ITEM>
      <ITEM>
        <ICON>icon-name</ICON>
        <HEADING>Feature Two</HEADING>
        <TEXT>Brief description</TEXT>
      </ITEM>
    </CONTENT>
    <IMAGE_QUERY>Modern icons representing technology or business concepts</IMAGE_QUERY>
  </SECTION>
  
  <SECTION layout="TIMELINE">
    <TITLE>Process or History</TITLE>
    <CONTENT>
      <EVENT>
        <DATE>2020</DATE>
        <TITLE>Milestone One</TITLE>
        <DESCRIPTION>What happened</DESCRIPTION>
      </EVENT>
      <EVENT>
        <DATE>2022</DATE>
        <TITLE>Milestone Two</TITLE>
        <DESCRIPTION>What happened</DESCRIPTION>
      </EVENT>
    </CONTENT>
    <IMAGE_QUERY>Timeline visualization with progressive stages</IMAGE_QUERY>
  </SECTION>
  
  <SECTION layout="CHART">
    <TITLE>Data Insights</TITLE>
    <CHART_TYPE>bar</CHART_TYPE>
    <DATA_DESCRIPTION>Brief description of what the data shows</DATA_DESCRIPTION>
    <IMAGE_QUERY>Professional chart or graph showing data trends</IMAGE_QUERY>
  </SECTION>
</PRESENTATION>

IMPORTANT NOTES:
- Vary layouts throughout the presentation
- Keep text concise (max 20 words per bullet)
- Image queries should be descriptive (10+ words)
- Maintain consistent tone: {{ TONE }}
- Use {{ LANGUAGE }} language for all content
- Ensure logical flow from slide to slide

